# Dataxx Front-End - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a front-end rebuild of the Dataxx platform - a sponsoring management platform for the sports industry. This project focuses exclusively on front-end development using Next.js, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

## Core Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Development Command**: `npm run dev`

## Critical Rules - MUST ALWAYS FOLLOW

### 1. Front-End Only
- **NEVER** modify or create back-end code, API routes, or server-side logic
- **ONLY** work on front-end components, pages, layouts, and UI/UX
- All API calls should be client-side only

### 2. File Organization - One File Per Entity
- **Every page, sub-page, component, utility, hook, type, constant, and style class MUST have its own dedicated file**
- No shared files containing multiple components or utilities
- Organize files logically in appropriate directories:
  - `app/` - Next.js app router pages and layouts
  - `components/` - Reusable UI components (subdivide by feature/type)
  - `lib/` - Utilities, helpers, and shared logic
  - `hooks/` - Custom React hooks
  - `types/` - TypeScript type definitions
  - `constants/` - Constants and configuration
  - `styles/` - Global styles and Tailwind configuration

### 3. MANDATORY USE OF REUSABLES - ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENT
**EVERY SINGLE THING MUST USE REUSABLES. NO EXCEPTIONS.**

#### CRITICAL RULE: ALWAYS USE REUSABLES FIRST
**BEFORE writing ANY code, styling, or value:**

1. **MUST scan the entire project** using codebase_search or grep to find existing reusables
2. **MUST check for:**
   - Existing components (Button, Input, Label, Link, Text, Heading, Container, PageContainer, Form, FormGroup, Checkbox, Card, Spacer, IconButton, HeaderSection) - **USE THEM, DON'T RECREATE**
   - Existing constants (FONT_SIZE, FONT_THICKNESS, COLOR, SPACING, BORDER_RADIUS, ICON_SIZE, LAYOUT, BUTTON_HEIGHT, BUTTON_OVERLAY, INPUT_HEIGHT, POPUP, OPACITY, SHADOW, Z_INDEX, TEXT_ALIGN) - **USE THEM, DON'T HARDCODE**
   - Existing color variables (COLOR.PURPLE, COLOR.BLACK, COLOR.WHITE, COLOR.GREY.*) - **USE THEM, NEVER WRITE HEX VALUES**
   - Existing font configurations (FONT_SIZE.M, FONT_THICKNESS.L, etc.) - **USE THEM, NEVER WRITE PIXEL VALUES**
   - Existing spacing values (SPACING.S, SPACING.M, etc.) - **USE THEM, NEVER WRITE MARGIN/PADDING VALUES OR USE TAILWIND SPACING CLASSES**
   - Existing border radius (BORDER_RADIUS.M, etc.) - **USE THEM, NEVER WRITE BORDER RADIUS VALUES**
   - Existing icon sizes (ICON_SIZE.M, etc.) - **USE THEM, NEVER WRITE SIZE NUMBERS**
   - Existing layout values (LAYOUT.CONTAINER_MAX_WIDTH, etc.) - **USE THEM, NEVER WRITE LAYOUT VALUES OR USE TAILWIND LAYOUT CLASSES**
   - Existing utility functions
   - Existing types/interfaces
   - Existing CSS classes or Tailwind custom classes

3. **IF something exists that can be reused:**
   - **MUST reuse it** - import and use the existing item
   - **NEVER create duplicates**
   - **NEVER hardcode values that exist as constants**
   - **NEVER recreate components that already exist**

4. **IF nothing exists that can be reused:**
   - **MUST request explicit user acceptance** before creating a new reusable item
   - Clearly explain what you plan to create and why
   - Wait for user confirmation before proceeding

5. **ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS - ZERO HARDCODED VALUES:**
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode colors** - ALWAYS use COLOR constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode font sizes** - ALWAYS use FONT_SIZE constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode font weights** - ALWAYS use FONT_THICKNESS constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode spacing/margins/padding** - ALWAYS use SPACING constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode border radius** - ALWAYS use BORDER_RADIUS constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode icon sizes** - ALWAYS use ICON_SIZE constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode layout values** - ALWAYS use LAYOUT constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode rgba() values** - ALWAYS use OPACITY constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode rem units** - ALWAYS use SPACING constants (1rem = 16px = SPACING.L)
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode opacity values** - ALWAYS use OPACITY constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode shadow values** - ALWAYS use SHADOW constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode z-index values** - ALWAYS use Z_INDEX constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode text alignment** - ALWAYS use TEXT_ALIGN constants
   - ❌ **NEVER hardcode component-specific dimensions** - ALWAYS use component-specific constants (BUTTON_HEIGHT, INPUT_HEIGHT, POPUP, etc.)
   - ❌ **NEVER use Tailwind spacing classes** (mb-8, mt-6, px-6, etc.) - ALWAYS use SPACING constants in inline styles
   - ❌ **NEVER use Tailwind layout classes** (max-w-md, min-h-screen, etc.) - ALWAYS use LAYOUT constants or components
   - ❌ **NEVER use Tailwind positioning classes** (left-3, top-1/2, transform, etc.) - ALWAYS use inline styles with constants
   - ❌ **NEVER use Tailwind flex/display classes** (flex, items-center, justify-center, etc.) - ALWAYS use inline styles with constants
   - ❌ **NEVER recreate existing components** - ALWAYS import and use them (Button, Input, Label, Link, Text, Heading, Container, PageContainer, Form, FormGroup, Checkbox, Card, Spacer, IconButton, HeaderSection)
   - ❌ **NEVER use raw HTML elements** for styled content - ALWAYS use reusable components
   - ❌ **NEVER write inline styles with hardcoded values** - ALWAYS use constants
   - ❌ **NEVER use className for spacing/layout** - Use inline styles with constants or reusable components

6. **Examples of FORBIDDEN practices:**
   - ❌ `style={{ fontSize: '13px' }}` → ✅ `style={{ fontSize: FONT_SIZE.M }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ color: '#5218F9' }}` → ✅ `style={{ color: COLOR.PURPLE }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ marginBottom: '8px' }}` → ✅ `style={{ marginBottom: SPACING.S }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ paddingBottom: '1rem' }}` → ✅ `style={{ paddingBottom: SPACING.L }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ backgroundColor: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)' }}` → ✅ `style={{ backgroundColor: \`rgba(0, 0, 0, ${OPACITY.OVERLAY})\` }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ boxShadow: '0 10px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)' }}` → ✅ `style={{ boxShadow: SHADOW.POPUP }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ zIndex: 1000 }}` → ✅ `style={{ zIndex: Z_INDEX.POPUP }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ textAlign: 'center' }}` → ✅ `style={{ textAlign: TEXT_ALIGN.CENTER }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ fontWeight: 600 }}` → ✅ `style={{ fontWeight: FONT_THICKNESS.XL }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ height: '40px' }}` → ✅ `style={{ height: INPUT_HEIGHT.MAIN }}`
   - ❌ `style={{ maxWidth: '600px' }}` → ✅ `style={{ maxWidth: POPUP.MAX_WIDTH }}`
   - ❌ `className="mb-8"` → ✅ `style={{ marginBottom: SPACING.XXL }}` or use `<Spacer />`
   - ❌ `className="px-6"` → ✅ Use `<Container />` component
   - ❌ `className="max-w-md"` → ✅ Use `<Container />` component or `style={{ maxWidth: LAYOUT.CONTAINER_MAX_WIDTH }}`
   - ❌ `className="min-h-screen"` → ✅ Use `<PageContainer />` component or `style={{ minHeight: LAYOUT.MIN_SCREEN_HEIGHT }}`
   - ❌ `className="left-3 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2"` → ✅ `style={{ position: 'absolute', left: SPACING.M, top: '50%', transform: 'translateY(-50%)' }}`
   - ❌ `className="flex items-center"` → ✅ `style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}`
   - ❌ `size={18}` → ✅ `size={ICON_SIZE.M}`
   - ❌ `<input className="..." />` → ✅ `<Input ... />`
   - ❌ `<label>...</label>` → ✅ `<Label>...</Label>`
   - ❌ `<a href="...">...</a>` → ✅ `<Link href="...">...</Link>`
   - ❌ `<p>...</p>` → ✅ `<Text>...</Text>`
   - ❌ `<h1>...</h1>` → ✅ `<Heading>...</Heading>`
   - ❌ `<div className="mb-8">...</div>` → ✅ `<HeaderSection>...</HeaderSection>` or use Spacer
   - ❌ `<form className="space-y-6">...</form>` → ✅ `<Form>...</Form>`

7. **Exceptions requiring explicit acceptance:**
   - New color values or theme colors
   - New font configurations
   - New reusable components
   - New utility functions
   - New constants or types
   - New CSS classes or Tailwind extensions

### 4. Code Quality Standards

#### Components
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Export components as named exports from their own files
- Components should be pure and reusable
- Use props interfaces defined in the same file or imported from types
- Keep components focused and single-purpose

#### Naming Conventions
- **Files**: PascalCase for components (e.g., `UserCard.tsx`), camelCase for utilities (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `UserProfile`)
- **Functions/Utilities**: camelCase (e.g., `formatCurrency`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `MAX_FILE_SIZE`)
- **Types/Interfaces**: PascalCase (e.g., `UserProfileProps`)
- Keep names simple, clear, and descriptive
- Avoid abbreviations unless widely understood

#### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript
- Define proper types for all props, functions, and data structures
- Avoid `any` type - use proper typing or `unknown` if necessary
- Export types from dedicated type files when shared

#### Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively
- Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary (then use CSS modules)
- Standardize color usage - reuse existing color values
- Create reusable component patterns, not duplicate classes

### 5. Project-Specific Requirements

#### Language
- **ALL text content MUST be in French**
- All labels, buttons, placeholders, error messages, and UI text must be in French
- This applies to all components, pages, and user-facing elements

#### Typography
- **Font**: Space Grotesk (loaded from Google Fonts)
- Must be configured as the default font in both CSS and Tailwind config
- Apply Space Grotesk to all text elements throughout the application

#### Theme
- **Default theme**: White/light mode only
- No dark mode implementation
- Ensure all components work properly in white/light theme

#### Responsive Design
- **Desktop-only application**
- Do NOT implement mobile responsiveness
- Focus on desktop/computer screen sizes (laptops, desktops, large monitors)
- Responsive across different desktop screen sizes is acceptable
- Do NOT code for mobile devices or small screens

### 6. Standardization Requirements

#### Colors
- Centralize color definitions in Tailwind config
- Reuse existing color values - never create duplicates
- Request approval before adding new colors

#### Components
- Break down complex components into smaller, reusable pieces
- Eliminate duplicate components
- Create shared component libraries for common patterns (buttons, inputs, cards, etc.)

#### Classes and Styles
- Standardize class usage across components
- Reuse common class combinations as components
- Remove unused or duplicate CSS/styling

#### Code Structure
- Keep files organized and clean
- Remove unused imports and code
- Maintain consistent indentation and formatting

### 7. Development Workflow

#### Before Making Changes
1. Search for existing implementations
2. Check for reusable components/utilities
3. Request approval for new reusables if needed
4. Plan file organization

#### During Development
1. Create one file per component/page/utility
2. Use TypeScript types properly
3. Follow naming conventions
4. Write clean, maintainable code
5. Comment complex logic

#### After Implementation
1. Ensure no duplicates were created
2. Verify French language is used
3. Check Space Grotesk font is applied
4. Verify desktop-only responsiveness
5. Test white theme compatibility

### 8. Prohibited Practices

- ❌ Creating back-end code or API routes
- ❌ Sharing files for multiple components/utilities
- ❌ Creating duplicates without checking for existing items
- ❌ Creating new reusables without user approval
- ❌ **Hardcoding ANY values** - colors, font sizes, spacing, border radius, icon sizes, opacity, shadows, z-index, rem units, rgba values
- ❌ **Recreating existing components** - Button, Input, Label, Link, etc.
- ❌ **Not using constants** - FONT_SIZE, FONT_THICKNESS, COLOR, SPACING, BORDER_RADIUS, ICON_SIZE, LAYOUT, OPACITY, SHADOW, Z_INDEX, TEXT_ALIGN, BUTTON_HEIGHT, INPUT_HEIGHT, POPUP
- ❌ **Using Tailwind utility classes for positioning/flex** - left-3, top-1/2, flex, items-center, justify-center, etc.
- ❌ Using English for UI text (must be French)
- ❌ Implementing mobile responsiveness
- ❌ Creating dark mode themes
- ❌ Using fonts other than Space Grotesk (unless explicitly approved)
- ❌ Skipping the reusable check before creation
- ❌ Writing inline styles with hardcoded values instead of constants

### 9. Required Checks Before Every Code Change

When requested to create or modify anything, you MUST:
1. ✅ **Scan project for existing reusables** - Check ALL constants, components, utilities
2. ✅ **Check if the item already exists** - Search thoroughly before creating anything
3. ✅ **Use existing constants** - FONT_SIZE, FONT_THICKNESS, COLOR, SPACING, BORDER_RADIUS, ICON_SIZE, LAYOUT, OPACITY, SHADOW, Z_INDEX, TEXT_ALIGN, BUTTON_HEIGHT, BUTTON_OVERLAY, INPUT_HEIGHT, POPUP
4. ✅ **Use existing components** - Button, Input, Label, Link, Text, Heading, Container, PageContainer, Form, FormGroup, Checkbox, Card, Spacer, IconButton, HeaderSection
5. ✅ **Never hardcode ANY values** - All colors, sizes, spacing, layout values, opacity, shadows, z-index, rgba, rem units must use constants
6. ✅ **Never use Tailwind spacing/layout classes** - Use inline styles with constants or reusable components
7. ✅ **Never use Tailwind positioning/flex classes** - left-3, top-1/2, flex, items-center, justify-center, transform, etc. - Use inline styles with constants
8. ✅ **Never use raw HTML for styled elements** - Use reusable components
9. ✅ **Never hardcode rgba() values** - Always use OPACITY constants
10. ✅ **Never hardcode rem units** - Always use SPACING constants (1rem = 16px = SPACING.L)
11. ✅ **Never hardcode font weights** - Always use FONT_THICKNESS constants
12. ✅ **Request approval for new reusables if needed** - Only after confirming nothing exists
13. ✅ **Create file per entity** - One file per component/constant/utility
14. ✅ **Verify French language** - All text in French
15. ✅ **Verify Space Grotesk font** - Applied everywhere
16. ✅ **Ensure desktop-only approach** - No mobile code
17. ✅ **Maintain white theme compatibility** - Light theme only
18. ✅ **Verify all values use constants** - No hardcoded pixels, colors, sizes, spacing, layout, opacity, shadows, z-index, or rgba values
19. ✅ **Verify no Tailwind utility classes** - All styling must use inline styles with constants or reusable components
20. ✅ **Use PageContainer for full-page layouts** - Or use LAYOUT.MIN_SCREEN_HEIGHT constant

## Remember
This is a clean rebuild focusing on:
- **Reusability** over duplication
- **Standardization** over inconsistency  
- **Clean architecture** over quick fixes
- **Explicit approval** over assumptions
- **Front-end only** focus

Always prioritize finding and reusing existing code before creating anything new.

